ALTHOUGH Mzansi is observing the 16 days of no violence against women and children campaign, women are still being abused and murdered.Noluvo Swelindawo (22) was sleeping with her girlfriend when she was dragged out of her shack in Driftsands, Mfuleni and shot.Noluvo&rsquo;s cousin, Nondoda Swelindawo, said a group of people beat up her cousin. Her badly bruised body was found yesterday morning.&ldquo;They took Noluvo and left her girlfriend behind.&ldquo;The girlfriend called us to let us know what happened,&rdquo; said the cousin.According to the Nondoda, Noluvo fought with a man at a local shebeen on Friday.&ldquo;The man and a group of friends beat her up on Friday and she couldn&rsquo;t go to work the next day. &ldquo;Then Noluvo&rsquo;s brother went after one of the guys who assaulted her,&rdquo; said Nondoda.She added that her family suspects the murder was a revenge attack by the man she argued with on Friday.&ldquo;She spent the day drinking with neighbours and later went to a shebeen on Saturday. &ldquo;She came back early but they followed her home, kidnapped her and beat her up before killing her and dumping the body.&rdquo;Police spokeswoman Constable Noloyiso Rwexana confirmed that the body of a 22-year-old woman was found near a bridge on Sunday morning.&ldquo;The victim had been shot. &ldquo;No one has been arrested at this stage,&rdquo; said Rwexana.Anyone with information should call the police on 08600 10111.